msgstr "Optimierungsalgorithmus"

msgid "[CROP] Specify how to deal with borders at movement compensation"
msgstr "Einstellen wie mit Kanten bei Bewegung umgegangen werden soll"

msgid "[INVERT] Invert transforms if checked"
msgstr "Invertierung der Transformierung"

msgid ""
"[RELATIVE] Consider transforms as relative to previous frame if checked, "
"absolute if unchecked"
msgstr ""
"Bewerte Veränderungen als 'relativ' zum vorherigen Bild wenn aktiviert, "
"'absolut' wenn deaktiviert"

msgid "Specify type of interpolation"
msgstr "Typ der Interpolation"

msgid ""
"[TRIPOD2] virtual tripod mode, equivalent to relative=unchecked:smoothing=0"
msgstr "Virtueller Stativ-Modus, Äquivalent zu relative=unchecked:smoothing=0"

msgid "Unsharp filter:"
msgstr "Unscharf Filter:"

msgid "Seek to a position on the video."
msgstr "Spule zu einer bestimmten Position im Video."

msgid "Make a snapshot of the video with the settings made."
msgstr "Erstelle ein Standbild des Videos mit den getroffenen Einstellungen."

msgid ""
"Set the snapshot duration from 3 to 15 seconds from the seek position, "
"default is 5 seconds."
msgstr ""
"Setze die Standbildlänge zwischen 3 und 15 Sekunden von der Such-Position, "
"Standardwert: 5 Sekunden."

msgid ""
"Set how shaky the video is and how quick the camera is. A value of 1 means "
"little shakiness, a value of 10 means strong shakiness. Default value is 5."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set the accuracy of the detection process. A value of 1 means low accuracy, "
"a value of 15 means high accuracy. Default value is 15."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set stepsize of the search process. The region around minimum is scanned "
"with 1 pixel resolution. Default value is 6."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set minimum contrast. Below this value a local measurement field is "
"discarded. The range is 0-1. Default value is 0.25."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set reference frame number for tripod mode. If enabled, the motion of the "
"frames is compared to a reference frame in the filtered stream, identified "
"by the specified number. The idea is to compensate all movements in a more-"
"or-less static scene and keep the camera view absolutely still. The frames "
"are counted starting from 1."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set the number of frames (value*2 + 1) used for lowpass filtering the camera "
"movements. Default value is 15. For example a number of 10 means that 21 "
"frames are used (10 in the past and 10 in the future) to smoothen the motion "
"in the video. A larger value leads to a smoother video, but limits the "
"acceleration of the camera (pan/tilt movements). 0 is a special case where a "
"static camera is simulated."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set the camera path optimization algorithm. Values are: `gauss`: gaussian "
"kernel low-pass filter on camera motion (default), and `avg`: averaging on "
"transformations"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set maximal angle in radians (degree*PI/180) to rotate frames. Default value "
"is -1, meaning no limit."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Specify how to deal with borders that may be visible due to movement "
"compensation. Values are: `keep` keep image information from previous frame "
"(default), `black` fill the border black"
msgstr ""

msgid "Invert transforms if checked. Default is unchecked."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Consider transforms as relative to previous frame if checked, absolute if "
"unchecked. Default is checked."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set percentage to zoom. A positive value will result in a zoom-in effect, a "
"negative value in a zoom-out effect. Default value is 0 (no zoom)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set optimal zooming to avoid borders. Accepted values are: `0` disabled, `1` "
"optimal static zoom value is determined (only very strong movements will "
"lead to visible borders) (default), `2` optimal adaptive zoom value is "
"determined (no borders will be visible), see zoomspeed. Note that the value "
"given at zoom is added to the one calculated here."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Set percent to zoom maximally each frame (enabled when optzoom is set to 2). "
"Range is from 0 to 5, default value is 0.25."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Specify type of interpolation. Available values are: `no` no interpolation, "
"`linear` linear only horizontal, `bilinear` linear in both directions "
"(default), `bicubic` cubic in both directions (slow)"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Enable virtual tripod mode if checked, which is equivalent to relative=0:"
"smoothing=0. Default is unchecked. Use also tripod option of vidstabdetect."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Sharpen or blur the input video. Note the use of the unsharp filter which is "
"always recommended."
msgstr ""

